==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gamble
<hw>Gam"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Gambled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Gambling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>game</ets>. See 2d <er>Game</er>.]</ety> <def>To play or game for
money or other stake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gamble
<hw>Gamble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To lose or squander by gaming; --
usually with <xex>away</xex>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bankrupts or sots who have
<xex>gambled</xex> or slept away their estates.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Ames.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gamble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gamble
<hw>Gam"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An act of gambling; a
transaction or proceeding involving gambling; hence, anything involving
similar risk or uncertainty.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gambler</ent>⟦br⟧
